===Etymology 1===
From the [[Hanyu Pinyin]] romanization of the {{bor|en|cmn|-}} for {{zh-l|肖|Xiāo}} and {{zh-l|蕭|tr=Xiāo}}.
====Proper noun====
{{en-proper noun|Xiaos}}
# {{surname|en}}.
===Etymology 2===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|cmn|-}} {{zh-l|小}}.
====Proper noun====
{{en-prop}}
# {{lb|en|in Chinese contexts}} {{n-g|Usually attached to a surname, signifying a little one, [[junior]], small guy, younger person.}}
===Statistics===
* According to the 2010 United States Census, ''Xiao'' is the 5669<sup>th</sup> most common surname in the United States, belonging to 6123 individuals. ''Xiao'' is most common among Asian/Pacific Islander (97.91%) individuals.
